==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marlin
<hw>Mar"lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
American great marbled godwit (<spn>Limosa fedoa</spn>). Applied also to
the red-breasted godwit (<spn>Limosa haematica</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[from <ets>marlin</ets> spike, the shape of its
bill.]</ety> <def> Any of several marine billfishes of the genera
<gen>Makaira</gen> and <gen>Tetrapturus</gen>, popular as game in sport
fishing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hook-billed marlin</b></col>, <cd>a curlew.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marline</ent>⟦br⟧
